Class OCLQuery

  • Object
    • MogwaiQuery
      • OCLQuery

  • public class OCLQuery
extends MogwaiQuery
    A MogwaiQuery implementation that wraps an OCL query to compute.

    Instances of this class can be created using the fluent OCLQueryBuilder API.

    Author:
    Gwendal DANIEL
    See Also:
    MogwaiQuery, OCLQueryBuilder

    • Constructor Detail

      • OCLQuery

        public OCLQuery(Object input,
                EClassifier context)
         throws QueryException
        Constructs a new OCLQuery from the given input.

        OCLQuery supports String, URI, Constraint , and OCLExpression inputs. If another input type is provided the constructor throws a QueryException.

        Instances of OCLQuery can be created using the fluent OCLQueryBuilder API.

        Parameters:
        input - an Object containing the input query
        context - the EClassifier representing the context of the OCL expression to compute
        Throws:
        QueryException - if input doesn't contain an OCL expression or if it cannot be cast to a supported input type
        See Also:
        OCLQueryBuilder
